Cell.Text: He was a dear friend of mine and a surprisingly astute pupil of academia... I was devestated when he was killed. | I suppose that risk always co-existed with his line of work, I just never thought his luck would run out.

Node.Caption: TG06EnthirGallusBackgroundBranchTopic: What can you tell me about Gallus?

Cell.Text: Well, for the thrill of course. | He was quite clear that he felt more in his element climbing through a window rather than hunched over a dusty tome.

Node.Caption: TG06EnthirGallusBackgroundBranchTopic01: He was an academic yet he chose a different path. Why?

Cell.Text: Ah yes, quite an amusing anecdote actually. I caught him trying to break into my laboratory. | I was about to show him the error of his ways when he made a curiously astute comment about my research notes. | I was astounded and in turn it lead to a conversation. Who'd have imagined it would lead to such a strong friendship?

Cell.Text: Besides the fact that there are only a handful of people in Tamriel that even recognize the language? | I'm fairly certain he was planning some sort of a heist that involved a deep understanding of the falmer language. | Sadly, we never had the opportunity to speak about the details.

Node.Caption: TG06EnthirAncientFalmerTopic: Why did Gallus scribe his journal in falmer?

Cell.Text: Ironically, I pointed him in the same direction I pointed you. To Markarth and Calcelmo. | I'm only hoping whatever means he used to learn the language will still be available to you.

Node.Caption: TG06EnthirAncientFalmerTopic01: Where did he acquire the knowledge to use it?

Cell.Text: In the time before man, they were known as the snow elves. They lived in the sunlight and had a very prosperous society.
Like the altmer? Yes, I would say their culture quite possibly rivaled our own.

Node.Caption: TG06EnthirFalmerBranchTopic01: So they were like your kind?

Cell.Text: [S] The Nords went to war with the falmer in the First Era. Killed them by the thousands to drive them from their snowy homeland. | The falmer retreated underground and forged an uneasy alliance with the dwarves who ended up betraying them. | This betrayal made them what they are now... horrible blind monstrosities with a burning hatred of any but their own kind.
Yes, I suppose you're right. Forgive me. I've lost several close friends to the falmer and it tends to distort my view.

Node.Caption: TG06EnthirFalmerFollowUpBranchTopic: They sound more like victims to me.

Cell.Text: Why shouldn't I? The falmer have killed more than a fair share of my acquaintances. They're animals... they show absolutely no pity or remorse.
Good. I lost more than a few acquaintances to the falmer and I wish to see them avenged.

Node.Caption: TG06EnthirFalmerFollowUpBranchTopic02: Then I'll make it a point to hunt them down.

Cell.Text: [S] If you wish to learn more about them, you're welcome to my tome on the subject. Should be on my table.
